<h2 id="using-kubestr">Using Kubestr</h2>
<h3 id="to-install-the-tool--">To install the tool -</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Ensure that the kubernetes context is set and the cluster is accessible through your terminal. (Does <a href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl/">kubectl</a> work?)</li>
  <li>Download the latest release <a href="https://github.com/kastenhq/kubestr/releases/latest">here</a>.</li>
  <li>Unpack the tool and make it an executable <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">chmod +x kubestr</code>.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="to-discover-available-storage-options--">To discover available storage options -</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">./kubestr</code></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="to-run-an-fio-test--">To run an FIO test -</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">./kubestr fio -s &lt;storage class&gt;</code></li>
  <li>Additional options like <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">--size</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">--fiofile</code> can be specified.</li>
  <li>For more information visit our <a href="https://github.com/kastenhq/kubestr/blob/master/FIO.md">fio</a> page.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="to-check-a-csi-drivers-snapshot-and-restore-capabilities--">To check a CSI drivers snapshot and restore capabilities -</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">./kubestr csicheck -s &lt;storage class&gt; -v &lt;volume snapshot class&gt;</code></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="roadmap">Roadmap</h2>
<ul>
  <li>In the future we plan to allow users to post their FIO results and compare to others.</li>
</ul>
